artists.biography: The Avalanches are an Australian electronic music group formed in 1997 with mainstays Robbie Chater on keyboards, Tony Diblasi on keyboards, bass and backing vocals, and Darren Seltmann on vocals and keyboards. They are known for their live and recorded DJ sets and their debut album Since I Left You (2000), which they claim was assembled from approximately 3500 vinyl samples. The album peaked in the top 10 on the UK Albums Chart in April 2001. At the ARIA Music Awards of 2001, the group received nine nominations and won four categories: 'Best New Artist - Album' and 'Best Dance Release' for Since I Left You, 'Best New Artist - Single' for "Frontier Psychiatrist", and 'Producer of the Year' for Bobbydazzler (production name for Chater and Seltmann). In October 2010, the album was listed at No. 10 in the book, 100 Best Australian Albums. The Album has also been named # 1 Australian Album of all time in a Triple J industry poll, as well as # 10 album of the decade by Pitchfork Media. It is estimated in the decade since its release the album has gone on to sell well over 1,000,000 copies.

raw_attributes.name: Wildflower

wiki.content: Wildflower is the second studio album by Australian electronic music group the Avalanches. It was first released on 1 July 2016 through Modular Recordings, Astralwerks, XL Recordings, and EMI. Production lasted 16 years and began around the release of their debut album, Since I Left You (2000). Pat Shannahan reckons around 50 samples were cleared for Wildflower commencing in 2012. The album contains 21 tracks and features multiple collaborators. The album was formally announced on 2 June 2016 alongside the release of its first single, an extended mix of "Frankie Sinatra". After the release of Since I Left You in 2000, the Avalanches continued to produce music. Over the course of a decade, the group worked on a wide variety of projects which involved collaborations with multiple artists. The album began as "ambient world music", and by early 2007, the band was considering over 40 tracks for an album which had become mostly hip hop oriented. The group became more involved in separate projects which pulled them away from the album. Some of their most time-consuming work included the score to a musical, King Kong (2013), and an animated musical film described as a "hip hop version of Yellow Submarine" which lost funding and was never completed. Wildflower features many remnants from these projects, but the Avalanches had to leave out many tracks which did not fit with the theme of the album. They plan to release these tracks at a later date. Read more on Last.fm. User-contributed text is available under the Creative Commons By-SA License; additional terms may apply.
